cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "ITU and Energy / Materials: A Single-Axiom View of Information-Energy Equivalence, Renewable Transition, New Materials, and the 2026-2050 Roadmap"
message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Terada
    given-names: Munehiro
    affiliation: Roboken
    email: munehiro.terada@roboken2.com
abstract: >
  We apply the Information-Theoretic Unification (ITU) framework
  (Terada 2026, DOI 10.5281/zenodo.20109209) to energy and
  materials science. Energy is reframed as K-work and information
  as K-bit; the Landauer-Bennett equivalence (E_bit = k_B T ln 2)
  establishes their unity. This is Tier 1 paper #10, extending
  the engineering wing to a pentagon (5 vertices) and completing
  the ITU 10-vertex polytope. Pass-1 progress: 82 of 220 phases
  (37.3%).
  Phase 79 establishes the ITU foundation. Compute energy per
  operation has dropped from 10^-3 J (vacuum tubes, 1950) to
  10^-17 J (GAAFET 3nm, 2024) - still 3,000x the Landauer limit
  (2.87 x 10^-21 J at 300K), leaving 3-4 orders of magnitude to
  exhaust. Battery technology Pareto: lead-acid 30 Wh/kg ($100/kWh,
  1860) -> Li-ion NMC 250 Wh/kg ($140/kWh, 2008) -> solid-state
  450 Wh/kg ($80/kWh predicted 2028). Solar cells reach 33.9%
  (Si+perovskite tandem 2024) toward Shockley-Queisser limits.
  Critical materials HHI: Gallium 9,604 (China 98%), Rare earths
  7,337 (China 85%).
  Phase 80 covers renewable energy + nuclear fusion. LCOE 2024:
  solar $40/MWh, wind $38/MWh (cheapest ever), vs gas $60, nuclear
  $182 (new build). NIF Ignition achieved Q=1.5 (Dec 2022) and
  Q=1.9 (2023, sustained). ITER targets Q=10 by 2035. SPARC, CFS,
  Helion, TAE pursue commercial fusion by 2030. IEA NZE 2050
  pathway: solar 50%, wind 22%, nuclear 9%, fossil 2% of world
  electricity. CO2 sweet spot: nuclear 12 g/kWh, fusion ~5 g/kWh.
  Phase 81 details the new materials revolution. Perovskite solar
  cells: 3.8% (Miyasaka 2009) -> 26.7% single (2024) -> 34.6%
  Si-tandem (2024) - 9x in 15 years. MOFs: NU-1501 reaches 7,140
  m^2/g (1.7 soccer fields per gram). Superconductors: H_3S 203K
  at 150 GPa (Eremets 2015), LaH_10 250K at 170 GPa (2019),
  room-temp candidate by 2030. AI material discovery: DeepMind
  GNoME (Nature 2023) predicts 2.2M new crystals; Microsoft
  MatterGen (2024) enables inverse design. Discovery cycle:
  24 months (Edisonian 1960s) -> 0.5 months (MatterGen 2024) =
  48x acceleration.
  Phase 82 synthesises into the 2026-2050 roadmap. Triple
  convergence: AGI accelerates research 10x, fusion + perovskite
  commercialize, China supply dominance diversifies (gallium 98%
  -> 60%, rare earths 85% -> 50%). EU carbon price $80 (2024) ->
  $300/t (2050). DAC capacity 0.01 -> 1,000 MtCO2/yr, cost $800
  -> $50/t. Ten falsifiable predictions issued. The ITU 10-vertex
  polytope completes: engineering pentagon (QC, AI, Crypto, Semi,
  Energy/Materials) + medicine triangle (Cancer, Aging, Psychiatry)
  + social sciences (Economics) + philosophy (Free Will).
  Central thesis: energy and materials follow the ITU axiom
  delta_S = delta<K>. Information-energy equivalence (Landauer-
  Bennett) connects Tier 1 #4 (Semi) to Tier 1 #10 (Energy).
  Pass-1 interpretive paper reframing Landauer, Shockley-Queisser,
  Lazard LCOE, NIF Ignition, perovskites, MOFs, GNoME in ITU
  language. Pass-2 work would derive ITU-specific battery
  chemistries or AI-discovered materials.
